==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin adiuvāns, present participle of adiuvāre, from [[iuvare|iuvāre]], to [[help]]. First English use recorded in 17th century.

===Pronunciation===
[[w:The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language|AHD]]: /ăj'ə-tənt/<br>
[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]: /'æd3ətənt/<br>
[[w:X-SAMPA|X-SAMPA]]: /{d3@t@nt/<br>

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# ''Military:'' A lower-ranking officer who assists a higher-ranking officer with administrative affairs
# An assistant.
# A member of the ''Leptoptilos'' genus of African storks, also known as [[marabou]].

